external_knowledge:
Recently updated datasets refer to those that have been updated within the last year; 
Demographic datasets are those that belong to the 'demographic' category; 
Datasets appearing more than once are those that have the same name and source but different dataset IDs.

sql:
SELECT AVG(df.file_size) AS average_file_size
FROM data_files df
JOIN datasets ds ON df.dataset_id = ds.dataset_id
WHERE ds.status = 'active' AND ds.year_id = (
    SELECT year_id FROM years WHERE year_name = '2020'
);
